reviewText: I love it. this one has the gardner museum.
Loved this series and this episode is no exception! Having this/and other episodes on DVD helps me deal with the fact that it is off the air! Good program!
Like the others of this line...excellent DVD.
Always enjoy any of the "America's Castles" videos.  They are well produced and this was reasonably priced.

Very educational.  It covers more than just the buildings.  It also covers a lot of American history as well.  We definitely enjoyed watching this and look forward to getting more episodes from this series.

Its not that is a bad DVD.  But please just two homes and of course its the two most popular homes George Washington's Mt. Vernon and Thomas Jefferson's Monticello... there had to be more then those two homes. Both are wonderful homes. However they should have added a unfamiliar home or called it the (Homes of our Presidents)..... if I where you  I would save your money OR buy it cheep.
